## Fairness Evaluation

Fairness analysis was performed across sensitive groups.

Example:

| Group  | Accuracy |
| ------ | -------- |
| Male   | 91%      |
| Female | 84%      |

The observed performance difference suggests potential model bias that should be addressed before deployment.

### Metrics Evaluated

* Accuracy by Group
* Error Rate by Group
* Demographic Parity
* Equalized Odds (where applicable)

---

## Bias Mitigation Strategies

The following mitigation approaches are recommended:

### Data-Level Mitigation

* Oversample underrepresented groups
* Collect more balanced data

### Feature-Level Mitigation

* Remove sensitive attributes
* Eliminate proxy variables that indirectly encode sensitive information

### Algorithm-Level Mitigation

* Fairness-aware training
* Fairlearn reduction techniques
* Threshold optimization

### Monitoring

* Continuously evaluate fairness metrics
* Retrain models periodically using updated data

